name: Corn-Stuffed Zucchini
author: RFaith
summary: This is one of my favorite recipes, shared by my best friend.
ingredients: 1 (8 ounce) package shredded Mexican cheese blend, divided
salt and ground black pepper to taste
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C)
Scrape the seeds and some of the meat from each zucchini and transfer to a bowl; add 3/4 of the Mexican cheese blend, corn, egg, salt, and pepper and mix well
Spoon corn mixture into the hollowed-out zucchini shells and arrange on a baking sheet
Bake in the preheated oven for 20 minutes
Sprinkle the remaining cheese over each stuffed zucchini and continue baking until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes
